column1: #Text=Melbourne is on East Central Florida 's Space Coast in Brevard County .
#Text=While most of Melbourne is on the mainland , a small portion is located on a barrier island .
#Text=The Indian River Lagoon separates the mainland from the island .
#Text=The island is a narrow strip of land that separates the Lagoon from the Atlantic Ocean .
#Text=Spanning the Indian River Lagoon to connect the mainland to the barrier island are a pair of four-lane , high-rise bridges -- the Melbourne Causeway and the Eau Gallie Causeway .
#Text=Serves Florida 's Space and Treasure Coasts with domestic and international passenger and air freight service .
#Text=Utilizing convenient , state-of-the-art facilities , the Melbourne International Airport is served by Delta and American Airlines as well as regional carriers .
#Text=The Airport also provides services including charter passenger flights , private aviation , and air freight flights .
#Text=Orlando International Airport ( MCO ) 64 miles NW of Melbourne .
#Text=Orlando-Sanford International Airport ( SFB ) 84 miles NW of Melbourne .
#Text=Daytona Beach International Airport ( DAB ) 90 miles N of Melbourne .
#Text=Space Coast Area Transit is the name of the local Brevard County bus service .
#Text=It is a cheap way to get around and is handicap accessible .
#Text=Buses travel to most sites and places of interest .
#Text=$ 1.25 per ride , or $ 35 for a monthly pass .
#Text=The best way to get around Melbourne is by car .
#Text=Harbor City Boulevard is the local street name , and it runs parallel to the Indian River on the eastern side of the city .
#Text=This road allows easy access to the beaches over 3 causeways :
#Text=the Pineda Causeway ( Florida State Road 404 ) , Eau Gallie Causeway , and Melbourne Causeway .
#Text=Locally named New Haven Avenue or Strawbridge Avenue ( historic downtown ) , US 192 is one of the major commercial , entertainment , and retail areas of Melbourne .
#Text=Many businesses , large and small , are located on this busy avenue .
#Text=It serves as a route to Kissimmee and the tourist corridor of Orlando to the west , and the town of Indialantic to the east via the Melbourne Causeway .
#Text=This 6 lane interstate highway passes through the city limits , 4 exit ramps located in the Melbourne Vicinity .
#Text=It serves as the main north-south route in the metropolitan area .
#Text=This road runs along the beaches and provides easy access to other areas of Brevard County .
#Text=Wickham serves as a second north to south route in the Melbourne area .

#Text=Journey deep into Forever Florida , a 4700 acre eco-ranch and wildlife conservation area , preserved just as nature intended .

#Text=This beautiful site boasts 9 distinct Florida ecosystems and an endless array of natural flora and fauna including alligators , black bears , nearly two hundred species of birds and the endangered Florida panther .
#Text=Choose your own fully-guided adventure : Coach Safari , Horseback Safari , soar through the treetops on the NEW Zipline Safari .
